## Zipkin Server

=================

Zipkin Server is used for distributed tracing in microservices architecture.

When a request passes through multiple microservices, Zipkin helps us track the complete flow of that request.

It helps answer questions like:

• How much time is taken to process a request
• Which microservice is taking more time
• How many microservices are involved in processing a request
• Where exactly the request failed

Zipkin provides a beautiful web UI dashboard to visualize request flow across services.

Zipkin Distributed Tracing Flow

Client Request
↓
API Gateway
↓
Service A
↓
Service B
↓
Service C
↓
Database

Zipkin records the entire request journey and displays timing for each service.

Zipkin Architecture
            +--------------------+
            |     Zipkin Server  |
            |  Distributed Trace |
            +----------+---------+
                       |
    ----------------------------------------
    |                |                     |
    v                v                     v

+-----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+
| Service A | -> | Service B | -> | Service C |
+-----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+

Each service sends trace information to Zipkin.

