## API Gateway

===============

API Gateway acts as the single entry point for all client requests in a microservices architecture.

Frontend applications cannot directly access microservices.

 all requests go through the API Gateway.

API Gateway acts as a mediator between the frontend and backend microservices.

Responsibilities of API Gateway

• Routing requests to the correct microservice
• Authentication and authorization
• Request validation
• Rate limiting
• Logging and monitoring
• Security enforcement

Filters and Routing
Filters

Filters allow us to perform:

Pre-processing (before request reaches service)

Examples

Authentication
Request validation
Logging

Post-processing (after response)

Examples

Response modification
Logging response
Error handling

Routing

Routing is used to forward client requests to the correct backend microservice.

Example

Client Request → /orders → Order Service
Client Request → /users → User Service

API Gateway Architecture
                 +-------------+
                 |   Client    |
                 +------+------+
                        |
                        v
                 +-------------+
                 | API Gateway |
                 +------+------+
                        |
    ------------------------------------------
    |                    |                   |
    v                    v                   v

+-----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+
| User MS | | Order MS | | Payment MS|
+-----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+

All client requests first pass through the API Gateway.

The API Gateway validates the request and forwards it to the appropriate microservice.

It acts like a security guard for backend microservices.


