If we use Rest Template  or Web Client we need to hard code the url of other service, which are not recomanded way because for load balancing we will deploy services in 3,4 places we will get 3,4 url's for single microservice so it's not good approach , better to go with Feign Client.

# Feign Client
----------------
By Using Feign Client we can establish the communication from one microservice to another microservice by using name of the micro service not by using url.

1.add feign client dependency to our project(user service(consumer))
2.@EnableFeignClients annotate on our main class(user service(consumer))
3.Create one Interface like below in consumer service

ackage com.userservice.controller;

import org.springframework.cloud.openfeign.FeignClient;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;

@FeignClient("PRODUCT-SERVICE")
public interface GetProductFeignClient {
    @GetMapping("/getProduct")
    public String getProduct();

}

4.Call this method from RestController class like below(user service(consumer))

package com.userservice.controller;

import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;

@RestController
public class UserController {

    @Autowired
    private GetProductFeignClient getProductFeignClient;

    @GetMapping("/getProduct")
    public String getProduct() {
        String product = getProductFeignClient.getProduct();
        return "User Service Called -> " + product;
    }
}

so here we are calling product service /getProdcut api from user service.



